Koch Hires Supertanker to Store Oil at Sea, Broker Optima Says

-- B y   R o b   S h e r i d a n
-- 
2011-06-30T16:51:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/koch-hires-supertanker-to-store-oil-at-sea-broker-optima-says.html
Koch Supply & Trading Co. booked a
very large crude carrier to store oil at sea, according to
Optima Shipbrokers Ltd.  Koch hired the British Purpose at a daily rate of $22,000,
for a period of 30-60 days, Optima said in a report e-mailed
today. Koch spokeswoman Mary Beth Jarvis declined to comment
when contacted by telephone in Wichita,  Kansas .  A VLCC can hold about 2 million barrels of crude. The
British Purpose has carrying capacity of 306,000 deadweight
tons, according to Optima.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rob Sheridan in  London  at 
 rsheridan6@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alaric Nightingale at 
 anightingal1@bloomberg.net  